<P>
BOYFRIEND STILL AT LARGE; 
</P>
<P>
MOTHER PLEADS NOT GUILTY IN TWINS' ABUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The mother of twin boys who were found beaten and abandoned at a Del Mar hotel 
pleaded not guilty Wednesday to charges of child abuse, child abandonment and 
inflicting corporal injury on the boys. 
</P>
<P>
Dorothy Denise DeSimone, 25, of Oceanside was ordered held in jail in lieu of 
$250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
The district attorney's office filed the charges Wednesday against DeSimone and 
her boyfriend, Charles Thomas McCoy, 27. McCoy remains a fugitive. 
</P>
<P>
No sex charges have been filed, despite earlier reports that the boys, found 
Saturday wandering at the Del Mar Inn, had been molested. 
</P>
<P>
A man suspected of being McCoy checked in with the 2 1/2-year-old boys earlier 
in the week. The occupant never checked out. 
</P>
<P>
The boys, who remain in Children's Hospital, had extensive bruises on their 
faces, some of which had been covered with makeup. 
</P>
<P>
The boys' uncle alerted police to their identities after seeing their pictures 
on television. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego Municipal Judge Charles Patrick ordered a bail review for DeSimone 
for Monday and a preliminary hearing for April 12. 
</P>
<P>
She was arrested after arriving at the hospital to visit the twins. 
</P>
