<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SCHOLARSHIP WINNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Elizabeth N. McNamee of Culver City High School, Victoria J. Edmond of the 
Marlborough School and Paul M. Magwene of Loyola High School are among 546 
outstanding black students nationwide who were named award winners in the 1989 
Achievement Scholarship competition. 
</P>
<P>
The winners were chosen from about 90,000 student competitors. They will 
receive scholarships financed by 120 corporations, foundations, businesses and 
professional associations and by large individual and group donations. 
</P>
<P>
The achievement program, which was established in 1964 by the National Merit 
Scholarship Corp., provides financial support to promising black students to 
further their education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
