<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
MIXED-USE DEVELOPMENT PROPOSED FOR OLD PIKE SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A proposal to turn the seashore site of a former amusement park into a 
sprawling complex of offices, residences and shops will go before the Long 
Beach Planning Commission this afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Pike project developers received approval for their 11-building proposal Monday 
from the Redevelopment Agency and are now seeking an amendment to the local 
coastal plan to allow construction of the mixed-use complex planned for the 
last large tract of privately owned land left in the city south of Ocean 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Proposed for just south of downtown, the project calls for 3.3 million square 
feet of new construction, to be built in four phases, ending in year 2003. 
</P>
