<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: W. LOS ANGELES; 
</P>
<P>
CAR-POOL LANE FOR FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Transportation Commission has approved $61 million for 
construction of a 26-mile car-pool lane on the San Diego Freeway from the 
Marina Freeway to the Orange County border. 
</P>
<P>
The funds are part of a $1.7-billion program to improve freeways and relieve 
congestion. Construction is scheduled between July 1, 1990, and July 1, 1994. 
</P>
