<TEXT>
<P>
Three Westside organizations were among recent recipients of grants from the 
Amateur Athletic Foundation of Los Angeles. The Santa Monica Gymnastic Center 
received $44,606 for new equipment; the West Los Angeles College Foundation, 
$41,800 to continue operation of the weight-throwing center at the college, and 
the Los Angeles School of Gymnastics, $40,000 for equipment and scholarships 
for rhythmic gymnastics. 
</P>
