<P>
TURKISH LAWMAKER SHOT TO DEATH IN PARLIAMENT SCUFFLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANKARA, Turkey 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A lawmaker from the governing Motherland Party was detained in the shooting 
death of an opposition member Wednesday inside Turkey's Parliament building as 
political tension ran high after a major setback for the ruling party in 
nationwide municipal elections last Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia news agency said that Abdurrezzak Ceylan, from the 
center-right True Path Party, died from a gunshot wound in the chest. 
</P>
