<P>
GAS BLAST KILLS ONE HOURS AFTER UTILITY CREW LEAVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOPEKA, Kan. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A natural gas explosion Wednesday leveled a house, killing one person and 
injuring two others, hours after utility workers made two stops at the 
residence, officials said. A KPL Gas Service spokesman said crews replaced a 
gas meter and repaired a leak in a pipe going into the meter, but had found no 
other leaks. 
