<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEAST'S BELLY BRINGS BACK BYGONE BAUBLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHANDIGARH, India 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A farmer whose water buffalo swallowed his wife's gold jewelry 12 years ago 
patiently waited for the animal to die a natural death, then recovered the 
baubles from the beast's belly, it was reported Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
When the unidentified farmer bought the animal in Kaithal, 50 miles south of 
Chandigarh, his wife fed it a traditional mixture of sugary flour from a basin 
that she had forgotten also contained her jewelry, the Chandigarh Tribune 
reported. The buffalo swallowed the woman's necklace, earrings and bangles 
worth about $2,000. Friends suggested that the farmer kill the animal to 
recover the jewelry, but he decided to wait until it died a natural death, 
which occurred Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
