<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY SERIES GETS EARLY START THIS SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Dodgers and Angels begin their final dress rehearsals for the regular 
season when they meet in the first game of the annual Freeway Series at 7 
tonight in Dodger Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The series, which starts a day earlier this year because the Dodgers open the 
season Monday in Cincinnati, concludes with games at Anaheim Stadium on Friday 
and Saturday nights. 
</P>
<P>
The Angels will close out their exhibition season Sunday against their triple-A 
farm team, the Edmonton Trappers, at Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Orel Hershiser, expected to start the Dodgers' opener against the Cincinnati 
Reds despite a recent bout with the flu, will split the pitching duties tonight 
with Tim Belcher. Mike Witt, who is scheduled to start Tuesday's opener against 
the Chicago White Sox at Anaheim, will start for the Angels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
