<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOOTHILL NAMES MCWHINNEY FOOTBALL COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBIE LUDOVISE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marty McWhinney has been named football coach at Foothill High School, Athletic 
Director Jim Ryan announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
McWhinney replaces Jerry Howell, who coached the Knights during the 1987 and 
1988 seasons. Howell resigned in February. 
</P>
<P>
McWhinney, 45, has been a voluntary assistant at Cerritos College the last two 
years, Ryan said. Before that, McWhinney compiled an 88-34-3 record in 12 years 
as coach at La Canada and El Rancho high schools. 
</P>
<P>
His La Canada team won a Southern Section Northwestern Conference title in 
1979. 
</P>
<P>
He will be on campus part time the rest of the spring and assume a full-time 
teaching position in the fall. BARBIE LUDOVISE 
</P>
</TEXT>
