<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
PERFORMING ARTS EXPANSION URGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A new survey for the Orange County Performing Arts Center recommends that board 
members consider building up to three new theaters, ranging from a drama 
theater for 650 or more to a concert hall with up to 2,500 seats. 
</P>
<P>
The study, prepared by Harrison Price Co. of Torrance and released this 
morning, found that the center's 3,000-seat Segerstrom Hall is operating at or 
near capacity. 
</P>
<P>
"The best way to relieve pressure on Segerstrom (Hall) is to construct a 
concert hall" at a cost of about $70 million, the study says, although "a 
lesser-quality concert hall . . . could be built for as low as $40-45 million." 
</P>
<P>
A drawback to the proposal, the study says, is that land next to the center is 
too small to accommodate such a hall, requiring construction at a different 
site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
