<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
MITSUBISHI GETS FSX JET CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Japanese government today awarded an $81-million contract to Mitsubishi 
Heavy Industries to design the FSX fighter plane, going ahead despite a lack of 
agreement with Washington on the controversial plan. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Defense Agency said the signing took place just one day 
before the end of Japan's budget year, which allows it to spend money allocated 
for the project in this year's government budget. 
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Heavy, prime contractor for the project, won a contract that 
includes groundwork for a design based on the U.S.-built F-16 warplane, said 
the spokesman for the agency, the equivalent of the Pentagon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
