<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
DIVORCE FOR NEWLYWED TESTAVERDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TAMPA, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tampa Bay Buccaneers quarterback Vinny Testaverde has filed for divorce from 
his wife of eight months and will seek a lump-sum alimony payment, according to 
court records. 
</P>
<P>
A document filed Wednesday in the clerk's office of the Hillsborough Circuit 
Court said the 1986 Heisman Trophy winner and his wife have been estranged 
since Jan. 26 when the marriage became "irretrievably broken." 
</P>
<P>
Testaverde met Laura Ann Gambucci in December, 1986, in Tempe, Ariz., when the 
University of Miami lost to Penn State in the Fiesta Bowl. He is entering the 
third season of a six-year, $8.2-million contract with the Bucs. 
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old quarterback requests a lump-sum alimony payment be a condition 
of the settlement. The court paper also stated that Testaverde and his wife 
have settled all claims against each other. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Vinny Testaverde 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
