<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CHINA ADVANCES IN TABLE TENNIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DORTMUND, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending champion China became the first men's team to qualify for the second 
round of the World Table Tennis Championships today. 
</P>
<P>
China, which has won the last four team titles, advanced with a 3-0 record in 
its group. The Chinese beat Norway 5-0 today with Teng Yi and Chen Longcan 
gaining two victories apiece. 
</P>
<P>
Sweden, seeded second behind China, also advanced with a 5-0 victory over Hong 
Kong. Sweden finished first in its five-team group with a 4-0 record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
